       (9366, 2, 7206, 18, 'General', 'Email', 'BNP - Step 2 - Reminder - 1 week prior to face-to-face interview',
        'Reminder: Complete Step 2: Pre Interview Submission', 'noreply@gov.nt.ca', '', '',
        '<div>Hello &lt;%title%&gt; &lt;%last_name%&gt;,</div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n\n<div>Please be reminded that&nbsp;you are required to complete the pre-interview submission in your online account a minimum of one (1) week prior to your interview. This includes uploading the following attachment:</div>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>IELTS or CELPIP language test results confirming that the prospective applicant has reached a level 4 in English against the CLB, or equivalent level in French.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n\n<div>As well, please be reminded that you must provide NTNP staff a summary of your business concept a minimum of twenty-four (24) hours prior to your interiew date. This can be done when you complete the&nbsp;&quot;Pre-Interview Submission&quot; in your online account, or you can e-mail a summary of your business concept directly to NTNP staff at the contact information below.&nbsp;</div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n\n<div>Please be advised that failure to submit these documents by the noted deadline will result in the interview being cancelled.</div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n\n<div>Please contact our program staff directly if you have any questions.</div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n\n<div>Thank you,</div>\n\n<div>&lt;%current_user_fName%&gt;&nbsp;&lt;%current_user_lName%&gt;</div>\n\n<div>&lt;%current_user_email%&gt;</div>',
        '2019-04-02', 'N', 0),
       (9367, 2, 7206, 18, 'General', 'Email', 'BNP -   Step 2 - Results of Face-to-Face interview - Negative Outcome',
        'NTNP -   Step 2 - Results of Face-to-Face interview', 'noreply@gov.nt.ca', '', '',
        '<div>\n<div>Dear &lt;%title%&gt; &lt;%last_name%&gt;,</div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n\n<div>Thank you for coming in for the face-to-face interview with NTNP program staff on&nbsp;&lt;%interview_date%&gt; in Interview Location Date.&nbsp; This e-mail is to inform you that you did not pass &ldquo;<em>Step2: Further Investigation and Face-to-Face Interviews</em>&rdquo;.</div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n\n<div><span style="background-color:#FFFF00">Although your proposed business concept is interesting and eligible for the purposes of the program, the NTNP does not feel that there is a substantial case for its economic viability in the Northwest Territories (NWT).</span></div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n\n<div><span style="background-color:#FFFF00">While you cannot move forward in the NTNP application process under the business concept presented in your face-to-face interview, I do want to note that you are an otherwise good candidate for our program.&nbsp; I would encourage you to continue to research the business environment of the NWT and present a different business concept for your application.&nbsp; Should you wish to continue to research further and present a new business concept, the NTNP will not require you to pay the application fee for a second time.</span></div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n\n<div>Please contact our program staff directly if you have any questions.</div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n\n<div>Thank you,</div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n\n<div>NTNP Business Stream</div>\n</div>',
        '2019-04-02', 'N', 0),
       (9368, 2, 7206, 18, 'General', 'Email', 'BNP - Step 3 - Expression of Interest (Positive Interview Outcome)',
        'NTNP- Step 3 - Expression of Interest', 'noreply@gov.nt.ca', '', '',
        '<div>Dear &lt;%title%&gt; &lt;%last_name%&gt;,</div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n\n<div>Thank you for coming in for the face-to-face interview and completing Step 2 of the NTNP Application Guidelines on&nbsp;&lt;%interview_date%&gt;&nbsp;. This e-mail is to inform you that you have passed &ldquo;Step 2: Further Investigations and Face-to-Face Interview (s)&rdquo;.&nbsp;</div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n\n<div>To proceed to &ldquo;Step 3: Initiating the Application Process and Pre-Screening,&rdquo; please complete the &ldquo;BNP Expression of Interest&rdquo; in your online NTNP account. Ensure that complete all sections and upload the following documents:</div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n\n<ol>\n	<li>Interview and Visit Event(s) Summary (applicants may wish to use the attached Appendix B: Interview and Visit Event(s) Summary Template in the Business Stream Application Guidelines).</li>\n	<li>A completed summary of your findings from the business trip to the Northwest Territories.&nbsp;</li>\n</ol>\n\n<div>Please note that you have <strong>sixty (60) days</strong> from the date of this e-mail to complete the&nbsp;<span style="background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255); color:rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family:arial,sans-serif,verdana,trebuchet ms; font-size:12px">&ldquo;BNP Expression of Interest&rdquo; in your online NTNP account.&nbsp;</span></div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n\n<div>If the Department of ITI:</div>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>&nbsp;is satisfied with the information provided;</li>\n	<li>approves the prospective applicant&rsquo;s business concept;</li>\n	<li>is satisfied the prospective applicant has the requisite business and communication skills;\n	<ul>\n		<li>based on the interview</li>\n	</ul>\n	</li>\n	<li>believes the prospective applicant is sincere in their desire to move to and settle in the Northwest Territories</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div>you will be invited in writing to formally apply to the Nominee Program, at which time you are to submit your formal business plan and undergo the Financial Verification.</div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n\n<div>We look forward to receiving the required documents in Step 3.</div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n\n<div>Thank you,</div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n\n<div>NTNP Business Stream</div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',
        '2019-04-02', 'N', 0),
       (9369, 2, 7206, 18, 'General', 'Letter', 'Appendix B - Visit Summary Template', '', '', '', '', '', '2019-04-02',
        'N', 0),
       (9371, 2, 7206, 18, 'General', 'Email', 'BNP - Step 4 - Invite to Apply to the Business Stream of the NTNP',
        'Step 4 - Invite to Apply to the Business Stream of the NTNP', 'noreply@gov.nt.ca', '', '',
        '<div>\n<div>Dear&nbsp;&lt;%title%&gt; &lt;%last_name%&gt;,</div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n\n<div>Thank you for completing <em>Step 3: Expression of Interest </em>in your application for the Business Stream of the Northwest Territories Nominee Program (NTNP). The Department of Industry, Tourism and Investment has reviewed the information provided &ndash; Congratulations, you are being formally invited to apply to the NTNP. A copy of your formal invite letter is attached in this email, and upon request can be mailed to you in hard-copy. Please see below for information on how to complete <em>Step 4: Submitting a Formal Application: </em></div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n\n<div>It is important to note that you have<strong> six (6) months from today</strong>&nbsp;to apply, and that only <strong>complete </strong>applications will be reviewed. A complete application consists of the following:</div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>A formal application requires that an applicant completes all sections of the&nbsp; &ldquo;BNP Formal Application Submission&rdquo; section of their online NTNP account&nbsp;and uploads all required documentation. The documents that are required for your formal application are detailed on the NTNP-03: <em>Business Stream Nominee Program Checklist.</em>&nbsp;The NTNP-03:&nbsp;<em>Business Stream Nominee Program Checklist</em> can be found here: <a href="https://www.immigratenwt.ca/sites/default/files/NTNP-03%20Business%20Stream%20Nominee%20Application%20Checklist.pdf">https://www.immigratenwt.ca/sites/default/files/NTNP-03%20Business%20Stream%20Nominee%20Application%20Checklist.pdf</a></li>\n</ul>\n\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>The <em>Third Party Financial Verification Report&nbsp; </em>and NTNP-04: Personal Statement of Financial Affairs form referred to in&nbsp;Appendix E of the Buisiness Stream Application Guidelines must be completed and submitted for an application to be considered. The <em>Third Party Financial Verification Report </em>must be completed by the accounting firm <strong>Crowe Mackay in Yellowknife or MNP LLP in Vancouver, BC</strong>. The applicant will work directly with either firm on obtaining their Financial Verification Report. Contact information can be found here:</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Celestino Oh (Partner, Crowe MacKay LLP)</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div style="margin-left:1.0in">+1-867-765-4411</div>\n\n<div style="margin-left:.5in">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<span style="color:#44546A"><a href="mailto:celestino.oh@crowemackay.ca"><span style="color:blue">celestino.oh@crowemackay.ca</span></a></span></div>\n\n<div style="margin-left:.5in">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<span style="color:#44546A"><a href="http://www.crowemackay.ca/"><span style="color:blue">www.crowemackay.ca</span></a> </span></div>\n\n<div style="margin-left:.5in">&nbsp;</div>\n\n<ul>\n	<li><span style="color:windowtext">Roy Tong (Senior Manager, Provincial Nominee Program Services, MNP LLP) </span></li>\n</ul>\n\n<div style="margin-left:1.0in">+1-778-374-2102</div>\n\n<div style="margin-left:1.0in">or <a href="mailto:NTNP@mnp.ca"><span style="color:blue">NTNP@mnp.ca</span></a></div>\n\n<div style="margin-left:.5in">&nbsp;</div>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Please ensure that your submission includes a detailed business plan outlining your proposed business concept. Details on the information that must be included in the business plan can be found under Appendix D: Business Plan Considerations of the Business Stream Application Guidelines.&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n\n<div>If an incomplete application is received, Nominee Program staff will advise the applicant that the application will not be assessed until all documentation is submitted. When an application is complete, an e-mail will be sent confirming that the application is complete and is now being assessed by Nominee Program Staff under <em>Step 5: Application Review. </em></div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n\n<div>In addition, should we have questions or need more information about your business plan, we will contact you separately.</div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n\n<div>Please contact our program staff directly if you have any questions.</div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n\n<div>Thank you,</div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n\n<div>NTNP&nbsp; Business Stream</div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n</div>',
        '2019-04-02', 'N', 0),
       (9374, 2, 7206, 18, 'General', 'Email', 'BNP -  Results of Step 5: Application Review - Negative Outcome',
        'NTNP -  Results of Step 5: Application Review', 'noreply@gov.nt.ca', '', '',
        '<div>Dear&nbsp;&lt;%title%&gt; &lt;%last_name%&gt;,</div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n\n<div>Please find the attached letter regarding the results of <em>Step 5: Application Review</em> for your NTNP application.</div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n\n<div>Please contact our program staff directly if you have any questions.</div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n\n<div>Thank you,</div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n\n<div>&lt;%current_user_fName%&gt;&nbsp;&lt;%current_user_lName%&gt;</div>\n\n<div>&lt;%current_user_email%&gt;</div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',
        '2019-04-02', 'N', 0),
       (9375, 2, 7206, 3, 'General', 'Email', 'BNP - Completing Step 5 and moving to Step 6',
        'NTNP - Completing Step 5 and moving to Step 6', 'noreply@gov.nt.ca', '', '',
        '<div>\n<div>Hello Mr. or Ms. &lt;%last_name%&gt;,</div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n\n<div>Please be advised that the NTNP has reviewed the business plan you submitted for your business concept.&nbsp; Congratulations, your&nbsp; application had been conditionally accepted into the Business Stream of the NTNP.</div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n\n<div>To move on to the next steps in the application process, we require the following:</div>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Sign and return the Business Performance Agreement (BPA) within 30 days of receipt. &ndash; <strong>Please note that the BPA will be sent to you in a separate email.</strong></li>\n	<li>Complete <em>NTNP-07: Business Stream Nominee Entrepreneur Deposit Form</em>; and</li>\n	<li>Make the required $75,000 Good Faith Deposit and provide proof of the deposit.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n\n<div>As per the BPA, within 2 months of the date that appears as the &ldquo;date signed&rdquo; on the Government of Canada temporary work permit issued, the Applicant must sit down with the Program staff and provide a completed <em>NTNP-08: Business Stream Arrival</em> <em>Report Form</em> and all required documentation, including proof of funds from a Canadian financial institution and thereafter must advise the Program staff of any changes to such information.</div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n\n<div>Please contact our program staff if you have any questions.</div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n\n<div>Thank you,</div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n\n<div>NTNP Business Stream</div>\n</div>',
        '2019-04-02', 'N', 0),
       (9378, 2, 7206, 18, 'General', 'Email', 'BNP -  Results of Step 5: Application Review - Positive Outcome (BPA)',
        'NTNP -  Results of Step 5: Application Review', 'noreply@gov.nt.ca', '', '',
        '<div>\n<div>Hello&nbsp;&lt;%title%&gt; &lt;%last_name%&gt;,</div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n\n<div>Please be advised that the NTNP has reviewed your complete Business Stream application, including the detailed business plan for &lt;%name_of_business%&gt;.&nbsp; Congratulations, your&nbsp; application had been conditionally accepted into the Business Stream of the NTNP.</div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n\n<div>To move on to the next steps in the application process, we require the following:</div>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Sign and return the attached Business Performance Agreement (BPA) to the program staff&nbsp;noted below; BPAs must be returned within 30 days of receipt.&nbsp;</li>\n	<li>Make the required $75,000 Good Faith Deposit via wire transfer. Details on how to complete the wire transfer can be found here: <a href="https://www.immigratenwt.ca/sites/default/files/NTNP07%20-%20Entrepreneur%20Deposit%20Form_2018_P1.pdf">https://www.immigratenwt.ca/sites/default/files/NTNP07%20-%20Entrepreneur%20Deposit%20Form_2018_P1.pdf</a></li>\n	<li>Complete the NTNP Good Faith Deposit Submission section in your online NTNP account and upload your proof of the deposit.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n\n<div>As per the BPA, within 2 months of the date that appears as the &ldquo;date signed&rdquo; on your Government of Canada temporary work permit, you must complete the BNP Arrival Report section of your NTNP online account and schedule the required arrival interview. When completing the arrival report section, please ensure you upload all required documentation, including proof of funds from a Canadian financial institution and thereafter advise program staff of any changes to such information.</div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n\n<div>Please contact our program staff if you have any questions.</div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n\n<div>Thank you,</div>\n\n<div>&lt;%current_user_fName%&gt;&nbsp;&lt;%current_user_lName%&gt;</div>\n\n<div>&lt;%current_user_email%&gt;</div>\n</div>',
        '2019-04-02', 'N', 0),
       (9379, 2, 7206, 20, 'General', 'Email', 'BNP - Step 6:  Business Performance Agreement & Letter of Support',
        'NTNP - Step 6:  Business Performance Agreement & Letter of Support', 'noreply@gov.nt.ca', '', '',
        '<div>\n<div>\n<div>Hello&nbsp;&lt;%title%&gt;&nbsp;&lt;%last_name%&gt;,</div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n\n<div>Please find attached your signed Business Performance Agreement (BPA) and Letter of Support for your temporary work permit application &ndash; Congratulations!</div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n\n<div>A couple of things to note:</div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>You have&nbsp;<strong>three (3) months&nbsp;</strong>from todays date to submit your application for a two-year temporary&nbsp;work permit to Immigration, Refugees and Citizenship Canada,&nbsp;or your Letter of Support as a NTNP Business Stream&nbsp;nominee candidate&nbsp;will be invalid. Please be advised that only in cases of exceptional circumstances will the NTNP provide a new work permit support letter.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Please advise the NTNP program staff when your work permit is approved and when you arrive in Canada &ndash; we require a copy of your work permit as soon as you receive it.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Within two (2) months of the date signed on your Government of Canada temporary work permit, you must complete BNP Arrival Report section in your NTNP online account and schedule your arrival interview. When completing the arrival report section, please ensure you upload all required documentation, including proof of funds from a Canadian financial institution. Thereafter, you&nbsp;must advise the program staff of any changes to your information.&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n\n<div>Please contact our program staff directly if you have any questions and if you would like hard copies of the BPA and Letter of Support mailed to you.</div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n\n<div>Thank you,</div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n\n<div>NTNP Business Stream</div>\n</div>\n</div>',
        '2019-04-02', 'N', 0),
